The paper deals with the computational complexity of propositional logics, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with the complexity of logical problems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely, as the paper deals with the satisfiability and model-checking problems, which are important in AI. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another likely category, as the paper deals with the computational complexity of logical problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper deals with the complexity of algorithms for solving logical problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also less likely, but possible, as the paper deals with the complexity of logical problems, which are relevant in some areas of machine learning.
